==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stable stand
<hw>Sta"ble stand`</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧nd`)</pr>. <fld>(O.Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>The position of a man who is found at his standing in the forest,
with a crossbow or a longbow bent, ready to shoot at a deer, or close by
a tree with greyhounds in a leash ready to slip; -- one of the four
presumptions that a man intends stealing the king's deer.</def>
<rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stabling</ent>⟦br⟧
